content.description: Originally referenced as Piano Keys, I changed the name slightly from the project name. Grab a high undercling and slopey slot and power over the bulge with improbable slopers to a distant knob and better holds. Shorter climbers will have a hell of a time getting up there. Groundscore (V11) starts down and left on the obvious rail and requires some heinous moves to join the standard start.
content.location: To the right of the prominent roof around the back of the boulder, look for the high undercling. Just left of a tree.

content.description: Start under the ceiling on two small slot crimps. Left of Groundscore and Right of The Diggler. Put your foot on and make a blind reach to the small crimp over the ceiling, fall into an undercling and jump to the jugs.
content.location: Left of Groundscore/Piano Man and Right of The Diggler. Two obvious slot crimps under the roof.

content.description: A fun and committing problem. Start on a high juggy rail with a heel hook, cross to a good sidepull and kick out left to the big flake. Follow the flake to its end and mantel into the groove.
content.location: On the Lifestyles Boulder, to the right of the roof with the El Jimmy problems, look for a big flake about 8 feet up.

content.description: The namesake problem of the Lifestyles boulder. Start low on the flake and make a huge reach for the crimpy rail, then go up with another crimp to a slopey cleft in the lip and mantel. Stand start from the crimp rail is V2.
content.location: On the side of the Lifestyles boulder opposite the big roof with the El Jimmy problems.

content.description: Sort of an eliminate but the moves are classic. Start at low jugs and slap right to the sloping corner. Stab for a tiny left hand slot then reach to the obvious rail over the roof, match, and shoot up and right to a jug underneath the upper bulge.
content.location: This line starts down and left of the prominent roof on blocky jugs and heads up and right using the holds described.

content.description: A nice line that's quite a bit tougher than it looks. Start with a good rail, lock off hard to reach tricky slopers, then rock up to the lip and mantel into the tree.
content.protection: A pad or two and a spot.
content.location: On the corner of the Lifestyles Boulder to the left of the Lifestyles problem (the side opposite the big roof.)

content.description: The massive Lifestyles Rock itself has many excellent problems on all sides, and there are several smaller boulders in the immediate vicinity with some good problems as well.
